         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">The herb sent is the Erythroea ¶ Typesetter's error for Erythraea ? ¶  Australis, closely allied to the British Erythroea Centaurium. It is an objectionable plant on pastures, because it is so bitter ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.01.00c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Leader</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Answers to correspondents', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>, 5 January 1895, p. 9 (B95.01.02). It is introduced by <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'</seg>
                     <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Specimen of Herb</seg>
                     <seg style="">.— F. M., Bong Bong.— Baron Von Mueller, reports:'.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bong Bong was a hamlet near Bowral, NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The herb sent is the Erythroea</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Typesetter's error for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Erythraea </seg>?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Australis, closely allied to the British <name key="Erythroea%20Centaurium">Erythroea Centaurium</name>. It is an objectionable plant on pastures, because it is so bitter that herds and flocks avoid it. But the bitter principle acts as a tonic like Gentian, so that a weak infusion or a tincture made with wine or diluted alcohol can serve medicinally. As the Erythroea is seeding copiously, and the seeds germinate readily, the plant should not be allowed to become abundant anywhere. It being an annual, it can be kept within bounds by cutting it before it matures seed.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Erythroea%20Australis">Erythroea Australis</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Erythroea%20Centaurium">Erythroea Centaurium</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
